                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d933">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">300.115(39)/369: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hamburg</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Keblinger</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hamburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-27T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 27, 1939—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>252. All vessels detained by prize control authorities en route to the United
                    States have now been released with the exception of steamships <hi rend="italic"
                        >Korsnaes</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Everoja</hi>, committed to Prize Court
                    proceedings, and Estonian steamships <hi rend="italic">Hildur</hi> and <hi
                        rend="italic">Osmussar</hi> and the Norwegian <hi rend="italic">Novasli</hi>
                    which are still being investigated. American bound consignments on Finnish
                    steamship <hi rend="italic">Dione</hi> and Estonian <hi rend="italic"
                        >Vaindlo</hi> (see Department’s telegram 207, and my telegram No. 241<note
                        n="18" xml:id="d933fn18">Neither printed.</note>) are also still being
                    investigated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Keblinger</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
